{"article_id":"8TzeyQLap2jgidze","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In a lengthy court filing Tuesday , attorneys for former National Security Adviser Michael Flynn alleged","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that then-FBI Deputy Director Andrew McCabe pushed Flynn not to have an attorney present during the questioning","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that ultimately led to his guilty plea on a single charge","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"of lying to federal authorities .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The document outlines , with striking new details , the rapid sequence of events","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that led to Flynn 's sudden fall from the Trump administration .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"The filing also seemingly demonstrates","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that the FBI took a significantly more aggressive tack","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"in handling the Flynn interview","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"than it did during other similar matters ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"including the agency 's sit-downs with Hillary Clinton and ex-Trump adviser George Papadopoulos .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"While Flynn is among several Trump associates to have been charged with making false statements as part of the Russia probe ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"no one","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"interviewed during the FBI ' s Clinton email investigation","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"was hit with false statement charges","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"- though investigators believed","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"some witnesses were untruthful .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"FALSE STATEMENT CHARGES ABOUND IN MUELLER PROBE , IN CONTRAST TO CLINTON CASE","depth":4},{"id":18,"text":"According to Flynn 's legal team ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"FBI agents in his case deliberately did not instruct Flynn","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that any false statements","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"he made","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"could constitute a crime ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and decided not to `` confront '' him directly about anything","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"he said","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"that contradicted their knowledge of his wiretapped communications with former Russian ambassador Sergey Kislyak .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"( Federal authorities","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"undertaking a national security probe","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"are ordinarily under no obligation to inform interviewees of their right to an attorney","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"unless they are in custody ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"as long as agents do not act coercively . )","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"FBI AGENT STRZOK ,","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"WHO INTERVIEWED FLYNN ,","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"DISCUSSED 'MEDIA LEAK STRATEGY","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"' If \" Flynn said","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"he did not remember something","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"they knew","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"they would use the exact words","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Flynn used , . . .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"to try to refresh his recollection , ''","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"FBI agents wrote in a so-called `` 302 '' witness interview report","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"cited by the filing .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"`` If Flynn still would not confirm what he said , . . .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"they would not confront him","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"or talk him through it . \"","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"McCabe","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"--","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"who was fired earlier this year","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"for making unauthorized media leaks and violating FBI policy --","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"wrote in a memorandum","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"that shortly after noon on Jan. 24 , 2017 , he called Flynn on his secure line at the White House ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"and the two briefly discussed an unrelated FBI training session at the White House .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Quickly , the conversation turned to a potential interview ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"according to an account","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"provided by McCabe","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that was also cited in the Tuesday filing .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"McCabe said","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"that he told Flynn","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"he \" felt","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"that we needed to have two of our agents sit down \"","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"to discuss his contacts with Russian officials .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"\" I explained","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that I thought","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"the quickest way","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"to get this done","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"was to have a conversation between [ Flynn ] and the agents only , ''","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"McCabe wrote .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"`` I further stated","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"if LTG Flynn wished to include anyone else in the meeting , like the White House Counsel for instance ,","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"that I would need to involve the Department of Justice .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"[ General Flynn ] stated","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"that this would not be necessary","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"and agreed to meet with the agents","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"without any additional participants . ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Explaining why Flynn was not warned about the possible consequences","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"of making false statements ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"one of the agents wrote in the 302","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that FBI brass had `` decided","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"the agents would not warn Flynn","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"that it was a crime to lie during an FBI interview","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"because they wanted Flynn to be relaxed ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"and they were concerned","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"that giving the warnings might adversely affect the rapport . ''","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"FBI INCORRECTLY SUGGESTED TO FISA COURT IN WARRANT TO SURVEIL TRUMP AIDE","depth":4},{"id":86,"text":"THAT YAHOO STORY WAS N'T BASED ON DISCREDITED SPY 'S REPORT","depth":4},{"id":87,"text":"The tactics were apparently in sharp contrast to the FBI 's approach","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"to interviewing former Trump aide George Papadopoulos ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"who also pleaded guilty to making false statements","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and was recently released from prison .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"In a court filing last year , Special Counsel Mueller 's team took pains to note","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that FBI agents","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"who interviewed Papadopoulos on January 27 , 2017","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"-- just days after the Flynn interview --","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"had advised Papadopoulos","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that `` lying to them 'is a federal offense ' ''","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"and that he could get `` in trouble ''","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"if he did not tell the truth .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"The revelations in the court filing ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"if accurate ,","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"would also sharply differ from the FBI 's handling of its interview with then-presidential candidate Clinton in 2016 , during the height of the presidential campaign .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"Clinton brought a total of nine lawyers to her interview","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"-- a number","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"that fired FBI Director James Comey said","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"was `` unusual ... but not unprecedented '' in House testimony in September .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"A scathing report","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"released earlier this year by the Department of Justice 's Inspector General","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"( IG )","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"found","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that the FBI had taken actions `` inconsistent with typical investigative strategy ''","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"by allowing former Clinton chief of staff Cheryl Mills and ex-campaign staffer Heather Samuelson to sit in on the Clinton interview","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"-- even though `` they had also both served as lawyers for Clinton","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"after they left the State Department . ''","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"In fact ,","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"the IG wrote ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"FBI officials fretted about how many FBI representatives should be at the interview ,","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"for fear","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"of prejudicing Clinton against the agency","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"if ,","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"as expected ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"she went on to become president .","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"\" [ S ] he might be our next president , ''","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"FBI attorney Lisa Page wrote ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"in urging","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"that the number of people at the interview be limited to four or six .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"`` The last thing","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"you need us going in there loaded for bear .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"You think","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"she ' s going to remember or care","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"that it was more doj than fbi ? \"","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"The IG report further noted :","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"\" Witnesses told us ,","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"and contemporaneous emails show ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"that the FBI and Department officials","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"who attended Clinton ' s interview","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"found","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"that her claim","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"that she did not understand the significance of the ' ( C ) ' marking","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"strained credulity .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"( FBI ) Agent 1 stated ,","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"' I filed that in the bucket of hard to impossible to believe . ' ''","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"FLYNN HAS PROVIDED 'SUBSTANTIAL ASSISTANCE ' ON CRIMINAL PROBE ,","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"MUELLER WRITES","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"In his fateful interview at the White House with since-fired anti-Trump FBI agent Peter Strzok and another FBI agent ,","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"Flynn `` clearly saw the FBI agents as allies , ''","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"according to one FBI 302 ,","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"which was dated Aug. 22 , 2017","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"-- nearly seven months after the actual interview .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"( The August 302 was from the FBI 's interview with Strzok about the January Flynn interview ;","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"a separate 302 exists for Flynn 's conversations .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"The Flynn 302 was approved by FBI brass in mid-February , three weeks after the initial interview at the White House . )","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"FBI MAY HAVE MODIFIED 302 REPORTS AFTER-THE-FACT ,","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"GOP REP SAYS","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"According to the Strzok 302 ,","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"Flynn was \" relaxed and jocular \"","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"as he gave the agents a `` little tour '' of his West Wing office .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"( McCabe reportedly testified later","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"that the agents ,","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"after speaking with Flynn ,","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"\" didn ' t think","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"he was lying '' at the time . )","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"In his report on FBI and DOJ misconduct during the Russia and Clinton probes , the IG additionally noted","depth":7},{"id":163,"text":"that Strzok ,","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"who was one of the two agents","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"who interviewed Flynn","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"and who was later also fired","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"for violating FBI policies ,","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"had compromised the FBI 's appearance of impartiality","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"by sending a slew of anti-Trump texts on his government-issued phone .","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"\" In particular , we were concerned about text messages","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"exchanged by FBI Deputy Assistant Director Peter Strzok and Lisa Page , Special Counsel to the Deputy Director ,","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"that potentially indicated or created the appearance","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"that investigative decisions were impacted by bias or improper considerations , \"","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"the IG report said .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"In one of those texts , Strzok wrote to Page in 2016","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"that Trump would not become president","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"because `` we 'll stop '' it from happening .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"SEVEN BOMBSHELL REVELATIONS","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"IN SCATHING IG REPORT INTO FBI , DOJ MISCONDUCT DURING CLINTON , RUSSIA PROBES","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"`` Even when circumstances later came to light","depth":9},{"id":181,"text":"that prompted extensive public debate about the investigation of General Flynn ,","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"including revelations","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"that certain FBI officials","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"involved in the January 24 interview of General Flynn","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"were themselves being investigated for misconduct ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"General Flynn did not back away from accepting responsibility for his actions , ''","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"Flynn 's lawyers wrote in the filing Tuesday .","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"Flynn was fired as national security adviser in February 2017","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"for misleading Vice President Mike Pence and other White House officials about his contacts with Russian officials .","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"In arguing","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"that Flynn should receive no more than a year of probation and 200 hours of community service","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"for making false statements to federal investigators ,","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"his lawyers Tuesday emphasized his service in the United States Army and lack of criminal record .","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"In a sentencing memo earlier this month , Special Counsel Robert Mueller recommended a lenient sentence","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"-- with the possibility of no prison time --","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"for Flynn ,","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"stating","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"he has offered `` substantial '' help to investigators about `` several ongoing investigations . ''","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"Meanwhile , Comey revealed in closed-door testimony with House Republicans on Friday","depth":6},{"id":200,"text":"that he deliberately concealed an explosive memorandum about his one-on-one Oval Office meeting with President Trump in February 2017 from top Department of Justice officials .","depth":6},{"id":201,"text":"The former FBI head also acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":202,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":203,"text":"when the agency initiated its counterintelligence probe into possible collusion between Trump campaign officials and the Russian government in July 2016 ,","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"investigators `` did n't know","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"whether we had anything ''","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"and that `` in fact ,","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"when I was fired as director","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"[ in May 2017 ] ,","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"I still did n't know","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"whether there was anything to it . ''","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"His remarks square with testimony this summer from former FBI lawyer Lisa Page ,","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"whose anti-Trump texts became a focus of House GOP oversight efforts .","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"Page told Congress in a closed-door deposition","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"that `` even as far as May 2017 ''","depth":11},{"id":215,"text":"-- more than nine months after the counterintelligence probe commenced --","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"`` we still could n't answer the question ''","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"as to whether Trump staff had improperly colluded with Russia .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":435,"left":302,"right":434,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":248,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":234,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":223,"right":233,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":221,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":0,"right":220,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":220,"left":1,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":227,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":6,"right":226,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":226,"left":7,"right":225,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":8,"right":224,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":11,"right":231,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":229,"right":230,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":228,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nu